es dans les STIM (Science, Technologie, Ingnierie et Mathmatiques) en Afrique Francophone a conduit Google  l’a nomm Mentor Women Techmakers pour l\'Afrique Centrale en 2020.  En 2017, Elle rejoint l’ONG Afroleadership o elle prend part activement aux formations en data journalisme et visualisation des donnes. De mars  septembre 2020, elle fait partie de l’quipe charge d\'assurer la transition numrique des enseignements  la Facult des Sciences de l’Universit de Yaound 1, ceci aprs la fermeture du campus suite  la COVID19.  Elle a suivi en fvrier 2020, une formation chez AIMS-Cameroun en Data science. Aujourd’hui Christelle est Analyste de donnes et  Formatrice chez Code for Africa.\nModerators\nCyprien Tankeu\nUniversity of Yaound 1\nGoogle Workspace Technical Lead\nSee Bio\nRaissa Mandeng\nWtm Douala\nWTM Abassador\nCcilia EKOMY\nP-C\nCEO\nSee Bio\nAnge Taffo\nWTM Ambassador\nWTM Ambassador for Limbe Cameroon\nSee Bio\nCHRISTELLE TANKEU\nCode for Africa\nData Analyst & Trainer\nSee Bio\n×\nCyprien Tankeu\nUniversity of Yaound 1\nCyprien is a computer scientist and GIS specialist. He is currently Google Workspace Technical Manager at the University of Yaound 1. With the Covid-19 crisis, he is supporting the University of Yaound 1 in their digital transformation process and online education. From December 2014 to June 2016, he has the honor to serve as Google Developers Mentor for Francophone Sub-Saharan Africa. During his mission, he worked with Tech Hubs, universities and local developer & startup communities to create and make grow a bigger ecosystem of developers, problem solvers and entrepreneurs of tomorrow.Before that,  He is since December 2011, Analyst at the Ministry of Arts and Culture of Cameroon. And since October 2014, Cyprien is lecturer at the National Advanced School of Posts, Telecommunications and ICT of Yaounde.\n×\nCcilia EKOMY\nP-C\nAuparavent en pleine formation de Comptabilit et Gestion des Organisations, C\'est une jeune femme qui a dcid de s